Detailed Description

Abstract class that represent a cell in the LocationHashTable.

The cell has functionality for finding an element at a specific location. Things to do in the subclasses:

  • The elementdata MUST be supplied by the subclass.
  • Support a method to add elements to the elementdata. This method can be called from a subclass to LocationHashtable.
  • Update nbrElements and the min/max members when neccessary.
  • Implement the three methods that calculates the distance by using the data at some index.
